  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I restore misc files from phone?",
  "response": "Restoring miscellaneous files from your phone can vary depending on the type of files you're trying to recover, the operating system you\u2019re using (Android or iOS), and how the files were deleted or lost. Here are some general methods to help you recover miscellaneous files:\n\n### For Android Phones\n\n1. **Check the Trash/Bin:**\n   - Open the file manager or gallery app.\n   - Look for a \"Trash\" or \"Recycle Bin\" option where deleted items may be temporarily stored.\n\n2. **Use a File Recovery App:**\n   - There are various apps available on the Google Play Store, such as DiskDigger or EaseUS MobiSaver.\n   - Download and follow the instructions within the app to scan for recoverable files.\n\n3. **From Google Drive or Cloud Backup:**\n   - If you regularly back up your files with Google Drive, check there.\n   - Log in to your Google Drive account and look through the folders, especially \"Backups\" or \"Google Photos.\"\n\n4. **Connect to a Computer:**\n   - Use a USB cable to connect your phone to a PC.\n   - Check the internal storage or SD card for any recoverable files.\n\n5. **Use a Data Recovery Software:**\n   - If you're unable to find your files, use dedicated data recovery software for Android, such as Dr.Fone or Recuva, following the provided steps.\n\n### For iPhones\n\n1. **Check Recently Deleted:**\n   - Open the Photos app and look for the \"Recently Deleted\" album where deleted photos and videos are stored for 30 days.\n   - For other files, check their respective apps as they might have a similar feature.\n\n2. **iCloud Recovery:**\n   - Go to iCloud.com and log in.\n   - Check \u201cPhotos\u201d, \u201cNotes\u201d, or other apps to see if your files are backed up.\n\n3. **iTunes or Finder Backup:**\n   - If you regularly back up your iPhone via iTunes (on Windows) or Finder (on macOS), you can restore your device from a backup:\n     - Connect your iPhone to the computer.\n     - Open iTunes or Finder, select your device, and choose to \"Restore Backup.\"\n\n4. **Use a Data Recovery Software:**\n   - There are several options available such as Dr.Fone or Tenorshare UltData which can scan your iPhone for lost files.\n\n### General Tips\n\n- **Act Quickly:** The sooner you try to recover deleted files, the better your chances are as data can be overwritten.\n- **Avoid Using the Phone:** If you know you'll be trying to recover data, limit the use of your phone to prevent overwriting the areas where deleted files were stored.\n- **Back Up Regularly:** To prevent future data loss, ensure you regularly back up your files.\n\nRemember, successful recovery can\u2019t always be guaranteed, especially if the files were deleted a long time ago or if new data has been written to the storage since.",
